International Brief -- Suntory Ltd.:
   Japanese Firm's 1991 Profit
   Before Taxes Declined 24%
Thanks to lower tax payments, net income edged up 4.8% to
5.1 billion yen from 4.87 billion on a 0.5% sales gain to
800.17 billion yen.
   Suntory's forecast for the current year is optimistic,
with unconsolidated pretax profit expected to more than
double to 22 billion yen.